<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-29T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-29T05:00:00-05:00" n="67" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d67">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/2381</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-29T11:00:00+01:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 29, 1915, 11 a. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2.15 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>341. Before declaring war against Turkey Italy will wait till opportunity
                            given Italians to leave Ottoman Empire. It is believed Greece will
                            advance immediately in Albania. Bulgaria seems present key of situation;
                            will probably espouse the cause of Allies if Italy sends considerable
                            forces to Dardanelles but at the moment Italy seems fully occupied with
                            Austria.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PTN1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>